### DeliveryTrack API Test File
### Use with REST Client extension in VS Code or similar tools

@baseUrl = http://localhost:5000
@token = YOUR_TOKEN_HERE

### Health Check
GET {{baseUrl}}/health

### 1. Login as Admin
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/auth/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "admin@delivery.com",
  "password": "admin123"
}

### 2. Login as Staff
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/auth/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "ramesh@delivery.com",
  "password": "staff123"
}

### 3. Get All Deliveries (requires token)
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/deliveries
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

### 4. Get Deliveries - Unpaid Only
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/deliveries?status=unpaid
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

### 5. Get Deliveries - By Staff (Admin only)
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/deliveries?staff_id=2
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

### 6. Create Delivery
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/deliveries
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "building_name": "Green Valley Apartments",
  "room_no": "A-101",
  "customer_name": "Rajesh Kumar",
  "customer_phone": "9876543210",
  "amount": 450.00,
  "description": "Diabetes medicine pack"
}

### 7. Get Single Delivery
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/deliveries/1
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

### 8. Mark Delivery as Paid
PATCH {{baseUrl}}/api/deliveries/1/pay
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "payment_mode": "cash",
  "note": "Collected in cash"
}

### 9. Get All Staff (Admin only)
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/staff
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

### 10. Create New Staff (Admin only)
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/staff
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "Vijay Singh",
  "email": "vijay@delivery.com",
  "password": "vijay123"
}

### 11. Delete Staff (Admin only)
DELETE {{baseUrl}}/api/staff/3
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

### 12. Logout
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/auth/logout
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
